## 🐛 KNOWN BUG — **404 NOT_FOUND on `/products` page (Vercel)**

> [!CAUTION]
> **This is the main bug to fix.** Screenshot was shown in chat.
> 
> **Error:** `404: NOT_FOUND | Code: NOT_FOUND | ID: bom1::mlqk4-1774924927437-760c91f0412e`
> 
> **URL:** `demo-easy-trade.vercel.app/products`
>
> **Root Cause:** Vercel deploys React SPA (Single Page App) but doesn't know to serve `index.html` for all routes. When user **refreshes** any deep route like `/products`, `/sales`, etc., Vercel tries to find a real file called `products` — which doesn't exist — and returns 404.
>
> **Fix Required:** Add a `vercel.json` at the project root (`d:\EASYTRADE\vercel.json`) with a rewrite rule to redirect all routes to `index.html`.

### Fix: Create `d:\EASYTRADE\vercel.json`

```json
{
  "rewrites": [
    { "source": "/(.*)", "destination": "/index.html" }
  ]
}
```

This is the **standard Vercel SPA fix** — one file, completely solves all refresh 404s.

After creating this file, run `push.bat` to redeploy to Vercel.

